In [19]:
# Extract month and year from the date
df2 = df.copy()
df2['year_month'] = df2['date'].dt.to_period('M')

# Calculate the average sentiment for each month
average_sentiment_by_month = df2.groupby('year_month')['average_sentiment'].mean()

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
average_sentiment_by_month.plot(marker='o', linestyle='-')
plt.title('Average Sentiment Over Time (by Month)')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Average Sentiment')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
In [20]:
# Calculate the sentiment counts for each month
sentiment_counts_by_month = df2.groupby(['year_month', 'sentiment']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sentiment_counts_by_month.plot(kind='line', stacked=True)
plt.title('Sentiment Counts Over Time (by Month)')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.legend(title='Sentiment')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

lda_model_pos = LdaMulticore(corpus=doc_term_matrix_text_pos,
                   id2word=dictionary_text_pos,
                   num_topics=6,
                   random_state=100,
                   passes=50,
                   eta='auto', workers = workers)

print(*lda_model_pos.print_topics(num_topics=6, num_words=10), sep='\n')
